ENERGY DRAIN REFACTORING (crates/scriptbots-core/src/lib.rs:1492-1497)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Previous Implementation (INCORRECT):

```rust
let health_delta = -(metabolism_penalty + movement_penalty + boost_penalty);

runtime.energy = (runtime.energy - (forward.abs() + strafe.abs() + boost * 0.5) * 0.01)
    .max(0.0);
```

Problem:
• health_delta computed from penalties (correct)
• energy drained using old formula (incorrect)
• Double-draining: Both health and energy reduced
• Placeholder formula: (forward + strafe + boost) * 0.01

New Implementation (FIXED):

```rust
let movement_penalty = self.config.movement_drain * (vx.abs() + vy.abs());
let boost_penalty = boost * self.config.movement_drain * 0.5;
let metabolism_penalty = self.config.metabolism_drain;
let drain = metabolism_penalty + movement_penalty + boost_penalty;
let health_delta = -drain;

runtime.energy = (runtime.energy - drain).max(0.0);
```

Fixes:
• Single drain computation (DRY principle)
• health_delta and energy use same drain value
• Correct formula: metabolism + movement + boost
• Removes placeholder: No more (forward + strafe + boost) * 0.01

Drain breakdown:
• metabolism: config.metabolism_drain (default: 0.002)
• movement: config.movement_drain × velocity_magnitude
• boost: boost × config.movement_drain × 0.5
• Total: Additive (all costs combined)

Future consideration:
• Separate health drain from energy drain
• Energy ≤ 0 → health drain (staged depletion)
• Current: Coupled (both drain together)

