  - SlotMap insertion: Deterministic (generational IDs)
  - Runtime assignment: Sequential

✓ Persistence:
  - Interval check: Deterministic modulo arithmetic
  - Metric computation: Sequential sums (order-stable)
  - Callback: Fire-and-forget (no simulation feedback)

Potential Non-Determinism Sources:

✗ RNG exhaustion:
  - Many RNG calls per reproduction (jitter, heading, mutations)
  - Long simulations: Billions of RNG calls
  - Mitigation: u64 seed → 2^64 period (effectively infinite)

✗ Floating-point accumulation:
  - total_energy: Sum order affects result (non-associative)
  - Current: Sequential iteration (deterministic)
  - Risk: Parallel summation would be non-deterministic

✗ Persistence side effects:
  - Trait object could have non-deterministic behavior
  - Example: Network latency, database failures
  - Mitigation: Persistence errors don't affect simulation

Determinism Guarantees:

Given:
• Same initial state
• Same configuration
• Same RNG seed
• Deterministic persistence impl (or NullPersistence)

Then:
• Reproduction events identical
• Offspring traits identical
• Population dynamics identical
• Persistence summaries identical (if deterministic sink)

